50|$|A <b>breast</b> <b>derrick</b> is a derrick {{without a}} boom with a mast {{constructed}} from two upright members. The upright members are more spread at their bottom ends than their top ends. There are crossbars {{to join the}} two members from the bottom to the top to form a mast. Without the use of boom, the top crossbar {{is also used to}} connect to a sheave or a block that is used for lifting the load. The mast is prevented from tipping forward by guys connected to its top.|$|E

